Xeroderma pigmentosum (XP) is a rare genetic disorder characterized by extreme sensitivity to ultraviolet (UV) rays from sunlight. The Xeroderma Pigmentosum Treatment market can be segmented based on treatment type, distribution channel, and end-user. In terms of treatment type, the market can be categorized into topical treatments and systemic treatments. Topical treatments typically involve the use of sunscreen and protective clothing to minimize UV exposure, while systemic treatments may include phototherapy or medications to manage symptoms. From a distribution channel perspective, the market is segmented into hospitals, specialty clinics, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Each channel plays a critical role in ensuring patients have access to the necessary treatments for XP. Additionally, end-users of XP treatments include hospitals, specialty dermatology clinics, and homecare settings, where patients can receive ongoing care and support for their condition.

